-- Home Depot completes sale of supply unit
-- 
-- Thu Aug 30, 2007 5:28pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/08/30/us-homedepot-supply-idUSWNAS322820070830

 

 (Reuters) - Home Depot Inc ( HD.N ) said it completed the sale of its wholesale supply business, HD Supply, to buyout firms on the same terms announced earlier this week. 

 The home improvement retailer sold HD Supply for $8.5 billion and would  pay $325 million to keep a 12.5 percent stake in the supply business. Home Depot also agreed to guarantee a $1 billion senior secured loan for the contractor business. (Reporting by Deepti Chaudhary in Bangalore)